  description="Circus and performance words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. TRAPEZE 18pts, JUGGLE 14pts, STUNT 5pts, CLOWN 10pts. Circus vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble circus words, performance scrabble terms, trapeze scrabble points, juggle scrabble, stunt scrabble word, clown scrabble, circus terms scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Circus Acts — Performance Terms That Score","description":"Circus and performance words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. TRAPEZE 18pts, JUGGLE 14pts, STUNT 5pts, CLOWN 10pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-circus-acts"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is TRAPEZE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! TRAPEZE scores 18 points (T=1, R=1, A=1, P=3, E=1, Z=10, E=1). The Z tile (10pts) makes it one of the highest-scoring 7-letter words. It means the horizontal bar used by aerial acrobats."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is JUGGLE worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"JUGGLE scores 14 points (J=8, U=1, G=2, G=2, L=1, E=1). The J tile (8pts) provides most of the scoring power. It means to continuously toss and catch objects in the air."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is STUNT valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. STUNT scores 5 points (S=1, T=1, U=1, N=1, T=1) and means a daring feat. While the score is low, its value lies in using common tiles and creating parallel plays on the board."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Circus Acts — Performance Terms That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The big top delivers big scores. Circus vocabulary hides some exceptional Scrabble words — TRAPEZE with its Z tile scores 18 points, JUGGLE uses the elusive J for 14, and even common words like CLOWN pack 10 points. These are words everyone recognises, making them easy to recall mid-game.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TRAPEZE (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JUGGLE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CLOWN</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">STUNT</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Circus Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">TRAPEZE — 18 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">T=1, R=1, A=1, P=3, E=1, Z=10, E=1 · 7 letters · Z power</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The swinging bar used by aerial acrobats. TRAPEZE scores 18 points — the Z tile (10pts) does the heavy lifting while P (3pts) adds support. At 7 letters, it's also a potential bingo candidate if you can extend it on the board.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🤹 JUGGLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · J=8, U=1, G=2, G=2, L=1, E=1 · Toss and catch</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🤡 CLOWN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · C=3, L=1, O=1, W=4, N=1 · Comic performer</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎪 STUNT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · S=1, T=1, U=1, N=1, T=1 · Daring feat</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔥 SWALLOW</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · S=1, W=4, A=1, L=1, L=1, O=1, W=4 · Fire act</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Performance Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ACROBAT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TUMBLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HOOP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WHIP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TENT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VAULT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Circus Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TRAPEZE is a 7-letter Z play:</span> Most Z words are short (ZAP, ZEN). TRAPEZE uses 7 tiles with Z embedded mid-word — perfect for reaching premium squares that shorter words can't hit.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JUGGLE handles the J tile:</span> J (8pts) is notoriously hard to place. JUGGLE pairs it with common tiles (U, G, G, L, E) for 14 points — and uses double-G, another tricky rack situation.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CLOWN pairs C and W:</span> C (3pts) and W (4pts) together in one word is uncommon. CLOWN solves both at 10 points from just 5 tiles — efficient and always playable.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Circus words solve the <span class="text-white font-medium">J and Z tile problem</span> in memorable ways. TRAPEZE (18pts) and JUGGLE (14pts) together account for 32 points — using both of the game's most awkward high-value tiles in words everyone already knows.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-jazz/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Jazz</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-j-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best J Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words for Scrabble</span></a>
        
